==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|ang|Æþelbeorht}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*Aþalaberhtaz}}, a compound of {{m|gem-pro|*aþalaz||noble}} + {{m|gem-pro|*berhtaz||bright, famous}}. It became popular in 19th century England due to Queen Victoria’s consort, Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha.

